---
alwaysApply: true
---

- All project dependencies must be declared in requirements.txt.
- Group dependencies with comments:
    # core data
    # streamlit ui
    # llm / api
    # testing
    # utilities
- Standard dependencies for this project:
    pandas, numpy, scipy, scikit-learn       # core data
    plotly, streamlit                         # streamlit ui
    google-generativeai, python-dotenv        # llm / api
    pytest, pytest-cov                        # testing
    pyyaml, python-magic                      # utilities
- Do NOT add openai, fastapi, uvicorn, or httpx — this project
  does not use them.
- Any new dependency must:
    - Be added to requirements.txt with a version pin (>=x.y.z)
    - Have a one-line comment explaining why it is needed
    - Be reflected in README.md technology stack section
    - Be reflected in docs/setup.md if it requires special install steps
- Flag any dependency that requires a paid API key or service
  with a comment: # requires API key — see .env.example
